Activity information includes activity types (running, walking, biking, etc), steps, calories, and accelerometer data. Body sensors provide access to data like heart rate, height, and weight. Google Fit will be able to access the activity and body sensor data stored by apps that connect to Google Fit. You can delete this activity information at any time in Google Fit Settings.
Activity and body sensor info can be managed in Google Fit and will be accessible to apps that have your permission.

Google Fit can use your location information to save routes of your activities and calculate information like your speed and distance. You can turn off location for Fit specifically and view or delete your activity sessions in Fit Settings.

"Location History helps you get useful information - for example, automatic commute predictions, improved search results, and more useful ads on and off Google - by creating a private map of where you go with your signed-in devices.
